Back in April 1989, the S-200 air defense system was shown for the first time on Soviet television.

It’s funny, but the reporting of that time is literally replete with the basic narratives of modern Russian TV - the latest air defense system... and this despite the fact that it was adopted for service in 1967.

Otherwise, the complex, which at first glance has outlived its usefulness morally and technically, has deep potential for further development with completely unpredictable functionality, especially taking into account the integration of modern technologies.

But today we only know about the following modifications, which I, as a real expert, will publish with light copyright from Wikipedia (non-experts just copy-paste):

S-200 "Angara" - V-860 (5V21) or V-860P (5V21A) missile, adopted for service in 1967, range - 160 km, height - 20 km;

S-200V "Vega" is a noise-proof modification of the complex, the firing channel and K-9M command post have been modernized, and a modified V-860PV (5V21P) missile has been used. Adopted into service in 1970, range - 180 km, minimum target altitude reduced to 300 m;

S-200M "Vega-M" - a modernized version of the S-200B, in terms of the use of a unified missile V-880 (5V28) with OFS or V-880N (5V28N) with a nuclear warhead (the V-880 missile defense system was developed after the cessation of work on the V -870). Solid fuel boosters were used, the far limit of the affected area was increased to 240 km (for a loitering AWACS aircraft - up to 255 km), the target height was 0.3 - 40 km. Tests have been taking place since 1971. In addition to the missile, the control panel, launcher and cockpit of the K-3(M) underwent changes;

S-200VE "Vega-E" - export version of the complex, V-880E (5V28E) missile, only OFS warhead, range - 240 km

S-200D "Dubna" - modernization of the S-200 in terms of replacing the ROC with a new one, using more noise-resistant missiles 5V25V, V-880M (5V28M) or V-880MN (5V28MN, with a nuclear warhead), range increased to 300 km, target altitude - up to 40 km. Development began in 1981, testing took place in 1983-1987. The series was produced in limited quantities.

What happened next, who knows... Everything is shrouded in darkness and ignorance...😎

